87,114.81,116.7,116.93,116.35,114.87,116.55,113.02,111.28,108.64,109.87,110.0,110.54,110.92,111.21,108.55,109.45,108.99,108.73,107.81,106.58,111.52,111.41,111.47,109.3,108.87,108.99,110.24,114.6,118.0,112.18,108.37,112.67,109.93,106.83,102.63,101.62,103.95,103.17,105.33,106.17,109.63,120.1,120.21,122.92,124.59,119.76,119.27,121.29,118.84,115.95,120.17,121.84,122.95]}},"formulas":{"returns":"Trailing point return = price[t] / price[t-N] - 1 (N = 21/63/126/252 trading days); adjusted total-return prices.","dist_from_52w_high":"price[t] / max(price, last 252d) - 1 (how far below the 1-year peak).","dma":"price[t] / mean(price, last N days) - 1; 'above' = price >= the N-day average.","drawdown":"current = price[t]/running-peak - 1; maxDD = min(price/cummax - 1) over the window.","liquidity":"median daily traded value (turnover \u00f7 1e7 = \u20b9 cr) over the last ~21 trading days.","relative_strength":"horizon: stock return - benchmark return (pp); line: (stock/benchmark) rebased to 100 over the last year."},"notes":{"source":"adjusted total-return price panel (bhavcopy-reconstructed) + NSE index TR + bhavcopy turnover.","frequency":"daily","confidence":"high where history is long; flagged low if thin/short.","why_useful":"what the market is saying about the stock \u2014 trend, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":66.4,"unit":"/100","status":"ok","read":"Average quality (66/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":1.62,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"1.62\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.02,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.02\u00d7, interest cover 15.7\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":18.03,"unit":"% YoY","status":"good","read":"Profit up 18% YoY (latest TTM) and accelerating.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":111.8,"pe_percentile":27.0,"median_pe":120.7,"earnings_yield_pct":0.89,"pb":3.99,"ev_ebitda":132.56,"quality_score":66.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":54.8,"peg":2.04,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 27-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 111.8\u00d7 earnings for ~55% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22482.04\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[58.18,59.83,61.07,59.48,59.9,59.64,63.7,64.19],"latest_pct":64.19,"chg_1y_pp":4.71},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[9.94,8.5,8.19,9.74,10.94,9.37,9.32,10.1],"latest_pct":10.1,"chg_1y_pp":0.36},"Public":{"periods":["Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[31.88,31.66,30.74,30.77,29.16,30.99,27.01,25.71],"latest_pct":25.71,"chg_1y_pp":-5.06}},"pledge":null,"events":[],"placeholders":[{"label":"Promoter pledge (detail)","note":"share-level pledge history \u2014 fetchable via NSE, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Bulk / block deals","note":"large on-market trades \u2014 NSE feed, deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Insider / SAST disclosures","note":"promoter & designated-person dealings \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"Exchange announcements","note":"NSE/BSE filings stream \u2014 deferred to MVP-2."},{"label":"